text: Anna Elendt (born 4 September 2001) is a German swimmer. She competed in the women's 50 metre breaststroke and women's 100 metre breaststroke at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. ==References== Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:German female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:German female breaststroke swimmers
